n that came with the oven. It&#8217;s a little deeper than a cookie sheet, so I usually pop it in the oven while preheating with extra water so it&#8217;s producing it&#8217;s own steam by the time the bread goes in.  Not as dramatic as throwing water on a hot pan, but it seems to work.</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\n\t\t<div class=\"reply\">\n\t\t\t<a class='comment-reply-link' href='/2010/09/no-knead-bread/?replytocom=54687#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm(\"comment-54687\", \"54687\", \"respond\", \"13427\")'>Reply</a>\t\t</div>\n\n\t\t</li><!-- #comment-## -->\n\n\t<li class=\"comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1\" id=\"comment-54690\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t<div class=\"comment-header\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"comment-author vcard\">\n\t\t\t\t<img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/41dc3e007986c35dc46763689fa93174?s=48&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2F0.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D48&amp;r=PG' class='avatar avatar-48 photo' height='48' width='48' />\t\t\t\t<cite class=\"fn\"><a href='http://www.blogger.com/profile/13272170681083008634' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Samantha</a></cite> <span class=\"says\">says:</span>\t\t \t</div>\n\n\t\t\t<div class=\"comment-meta commentmetadata\">\n\t\t\t\t<a href=\"http://www.budgetbytes.com/2010/09/no-knead-bread/#comment-54690\">09.16.10 at 3:24 pm</a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div>\n\n\t\t<div class=\"comment-content\">\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t<p>I have stayed away from making bread because I hate having to knead it. Now I do not have to worry! Thanks for sharing this recipe.</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\n\t\t<div class=\"reply\">\n\t\t\t<a class='comment-reply-link' href='/2010/09/no-knead-bread/?replytocom=54690#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm(\"comment-54690\", \"54690\", \"respond\", \"13427\")'>Reply</a>\t\t</div>\n\n\t\t</li><!-- #comment-## -->\n\n\t<li class=\"comment even thread-even depth-1\" id=\"comment-54691\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t<div class=\"comment-header\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"comment-