n fresh yeast?  Is it possible to use dried yeast with this recipe?</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\n\t\t<div class=\"reply\">\n\t\t\t<a class='comment-reply-link' href='/2010/09/no-knead-bread/?replytocom=58731#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm(\"comment-58731\", \"58731\", \"respond\", \"13427\")'>Reply</a>\t\t</div>\n\n\t\t</li><!-- #comment-## -->\n\n\t<li class=\"comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1\" id=\"comment-58842\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t<div class=\"comment-header\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"comment-author vcard\">\n\t\t\t\t<img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/41dc3e007986c35dc46763689fa93174?s=48&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2F0.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D48&amp;r=PG' class='avatar avatar-48 photo' height='48' width='48' />\t\t\t\t<cite class=\"fn\"><a href='http://www.blogger.com/profile/08315945586819945047' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Beth M</a></cite> <span class=\"says\">says:</span>\t\t \t</div>\n\n\t\t\t<div class=\"comment-meta commentmetadata\">\n\t\t\t\t<a href=\"http://www.budgetbytes.com/2010/09/no-knead-bread/#comment-58842\">11.10.11 at 5:54 pm</a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div>\n\n\t\t<div class=\"comment-content\">\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t<p>Claire &#8211; Actually, I only use dry yeast!  I usually buy a small jar of the instant yeast because that&#8217;s where I get the most bang for my buck.  I keep it in the refrigerator and it stays good for months.  I&#8217;m not really familiar with fresh yeast so I don&#8217;t know what to suggest&#8230; but if you use dry yeast, make sure to use &#8220;instant&#8221; or &#8220;bread machine&#8221; yeast because neither of those need to be dissolved in water before adding to a recipe.</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\n\t\t<div class=\"reply\">\n\t\t\t<a class='comment-reply-link' href='/2010/09/no-knead-bread/?replytocom=58842#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm(\"comment-58842\", \"58842\", \"respond\", \"13427\")'>Reply</a>\t\t</div>\n\n\t\t</li><!-- #comment-## -->\n\n\t<l