ng one) and the water pans heat up with the oven. When the oven is ready to go, slide the risen loaf onto the stone and pour about one cup of water into the water pan below. Cook for about 30 minutes or until the crust is a nice medium brown in color.", "Be sure to let the loaf cool before cutting into it otherwise you\u2019ll have a gummy crumb."], "images": [{"url": "http://lh3.ggpht.com/_OaYG005JPDs/TJEiLpIjX6I/AAAAAAAAB40/p3FDioTHiA4/s640/5%20minute%20bread%20angle.jpg", "path": "full/9a1d4c261f680ff09e54cc1b941440c870959ca3.jpg", "checksum": "2fc71efb35a5dd8c7dfcbf785e26476f"}], "link": "http://www.budgetbytes.com/2010/09/no-knead-bread/", "recipe_cook_time": ["PT30M"], "recipe_yield": ["2 small loaves"]}